The article is written by Bernie Marcus and it emphasizes the need for Republican senators to unite and pass tax cuts for hardworking Americans. The author highlights the benefits of the tax cuts, such as the doubling of the zero tax rate, the doubling of the child tax credit, and the elimination of the 15 percent tax bracket. Marcus also mentions the new deduction for businesses earning less than $500,000 annually, which would provide relief for small-business job creators. The author argues that tax cuts are more than just a Christmas gift, as they have positive long-term effects. Marcus believes that senators who support the tax cut bill will be remembered and thanked by their constituents. The article concludes by urging Republican senators to set aside political differences and come together for the benefit of hardworking Americans.